[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking at how the pooled factory closes objects using p.getObject().close() when the pool is closed. It seems like the close method should increment properly. I need to think about invalidation and ensuring that the wrapped close method returns objects to the pool. I’ll check if GenericObjectPool's close method invokes destroyObject for idle connections as well. I also need to consider the implementations of certain methods for RedisCommands, like how to handle ping.
