mmand handling**\\n\\nI’m looking at a potential issue where the native image can't proxy large Redis commands. It seems like using metadata could help, but there’s reflection involved in invoking commands. The agent captures these interactions. I’m considering using a real RedisClient to simplify things, although it requires a dedicated server. Another option is to use ConnectionPoolSupport, which would need some dependencies. I’ll need to ensure all tests compile and check Gradle settings as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering connection pooling**\\n\\nI’m looking at how the pooled factory closes objects using p.getObject().close() when the pool is closed. It seems like the close method should increment properly. I need to think about invalidation and ensuring that the wrapped close method returns objects to the pool. I’ll check if GenericObjectPool's close method invokes destroyObject for idle connections as well. I also need to consider the implementations of certain methods for RedisCommands, like how to handle ping.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hiDlSYDldANepCqCIWzO3hmy|fc_0d96ffd012e84abf0169f9ba9200e4819f84309d05c5b4084e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"commons-pool\" -n tests/src/io.lettuce/lettuce-core metadata/io.lettuce || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1222, "output": 1296, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28118, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777973886309, "responseId": "resp_0d96ffd012e84abf0169f9ba7ed8f4819f9a9ff5cb28582930"}}
